oposed model formulation and show results of\nretrospective fitting to incidence rates and forward planning with relevant\n``what if/instead of'' lockdown counterfactuals with uncertainty\nquantification. Our formulation is agnostic to a specific locale, in that\nlockdown strategies in other regions can be straightforwardly encoded using\nthis model. The methods we describe are made publicly available online through\nan accessible and easy to use web interface.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Jun 2021 13:30:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-19"}
